## Storage layout

{{STORAGE}}

<!--
  Key → meaning, owner, TTL. Example:

  | Key                     | Stored in           | Owner            | Notes |
  |-------------------------|---------------------|------------------|-------|
  | settings                | chrome.storage.sync | options page     | Cross-device sync |
  | cache:<hash>            | chrome.storage.local | content script   | Manual eviction; no TTL |
  | session:tabId:<n>       | chrome.storage.session | service worker | Cleared on browser close (MV3) |

  Note that `chrome.storage` is async; localStorage is sync but isolated per origin.
-->

## Common pitfalls

{{PITFALLS}}

<!--
  - Module-level state in the service worker disappears on restart. Persist anything
    you need across firings.
  - Content script and page JS do NOT share globals — page-world `window.X` is invisible.
  - MV3 disallows remote-loaded JS; bundle everything.
  - `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` returns a Promise (MV3); the callback form is MV2-only.
  - host_permissions added later requires a re-grant flow on Chrome — surface this in
    the options UI.
  - Other gotchas observed in this project's code.
-->
